      </description_type>
   </description>
   <description>
      <description_text xml:lang="en">Reconstructed invariant mass distributions of the hadronic W (jj') boson
and top quark (jj'b) candidates in each b jet category. The kinematic variables
describe the $\ell$+jets decay channel, where $\ell$ can be either a muon ($\mu$)
or electron ($\rm{e}$). The measured cross sections are given per decay channel
and for their combination.

The fiducial region is defined as:
- $\equiv$1lepton, $p_T$&gt;30GeV&amp;&amp;|$\eta$|&lt;2.1
- exluding 1.444&lt;|$\eta$|&lt;1.566 region only in the $\rm{e}$+jets channel
- no additional lepton with $p_T$&gt;20GeV&amp;&amp;|$\eta$|&lt;2.5 and $p_T$&gt;15GeV&amp;&amp;|$\eta$|&lt;2.4 in the $\mu$+jets and $\rm{e}$+jets channel, respectively
- $\geq$4jets(anti-kt,R=0.4), $p_T$&gt;25GeV&amp;&amp;|$\eta$|&lt;2.5
- min($\Delta R(jet,\ell)$) &gt; 0.3
- ambiguities in pairing the jj' are resolved by choosing the combination that results in the smaller value of the $\Delta R(j,j')$, where $\Delta R=\sqrt{ (\Delta \eta)^{2} + (\Delta \phi)^{2}}$
- ambiguities in pairing the jj'b are resolved by choosing the combination that results in the smaller value of the $|m_{jj'b}-m_{\ell\nu b}|$

The acceptance is measured in the $\mu$+jets channel as:
0.060$\pm$0.002(tot)

The acceptance is measured in the $\rm{e}$+jets channel as:
0.056$\pm$0.002(tot)

The efficiency is measured in the $\mu$+jets channel as:
0.91$\pm$0.04(tot)

The efficiency is measured in the $\rm{e}$+jets channel as:
0.63$\pm$0.03(tot)
</description_text>
